## .rule = forbid-term-dryrun

### .what
forbid term dryrun (variants: dry-run, dry_run, dryRun)

### .scope
- code: variable names, function names, parameters, comments
- files: filenames, directory names
- docs: markdown, briefs, prompts
- comms: commit messages, pr descriptions

### .why
- double negatives: dryRun: false means do it, unclear
- boolean limits extensibility: can't add modes like VALIDATE or DIFF
- unclear semantics: dry run jargon; use self-evident terms like PLAN and APPLY

### .enforcement
use of dryrun variants = blocker

### .pattern
use: mode: 'PLAN' | 'APPLY'

```ts
// instead of
const result = await deploy({ dryRun: true });  // ğŸ‘
const result = await deploy({ dryRun: false }); // ğŸ‘

// use
const result = await deploy({ mode: 'PLAN' });  // ğŸ‘
const result = await deploy({ mode: 'APPLY' }); // ğŸ‘
```

### .extensibility
enum scales: type DeployMode = 'PLAN' | 'VALIDATE' | 'DIFF' | 'APPLY'

```ts
const result = await deploy({ mode: 'DIFF' });
```

### .common usecases

| ğŸ‘ dryrun pattern | ğŸ‘ mode pattern |
| ----------------- | --------------- |
| dryRun: true     | mode: 'PLAN'   |
| dryRun: false    | mode: 'APPLY'  |
| --dry-run flag   | --mode plan    |
| DRY_RUN=1 env    | MODE=plan env  |

